name: McDonald's
description: Classic, long-running fast-food chain known for its burgers & fries.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Worst ever.  Asked for no cheese and they still messed it up.  Tried to scrape it off but they gave me NO napkins In the bag AND none available in the restaurant.  Fries are under cooked and they were busy so I guess someone took it out early.

What a waste of my money.  Tried to eat it as I was hungry and did not have breakfast.  Considering what they gave me.  I will stay hungry.
Coke was good

featured_reviews.review_id:
Dear McDonalds Canada,

We are a frequent customers of your franchises in and around Vancouver. Each time we visit, we don't just go in to get free food. We spend X amount of money each time to get our food. And this particular franchise employees were absolutely rude and disrespectful in their service to us. We ordered our food at the kiosk in store at 9:58 pm and got our food delivered after 45 mins. It was a total mess, on top of it there was a missing item. When asked for it, the manager asked us, if we were arguing just for the "sake of a single milkshake"??!! You kept us waiting for so long, our food wasn't delivered in a good way, there was a missing item and the poutine tasted horrible. Do you really think a customer who spends so much of money to buy food from your store and gets such a horrible experience would be happy with your brand?! The managers were so rude. They just wanted to refund the amount and kick us out and were not at all ready to talk. Really?? Do you think that would have made my child happy who slept off while waiting for the food??

Please train your employees or assign more employees to serve the customers who walk in to order their food in store, as much as they prioritise the drive through orders. Also, please train this particular manager how to deal with an unhappy customer. She was ABSOLUTELY RUDE. Her behaviour was a nonsense. It was very frustrating and insulting. She literally asked us to pick us things and get out. I have her picture with me. Please reach out and I can share her picture to help trace her down.

I'm really hoping that you would take care of this. Please do not provide such a bad customer experience. It is very annoying and spoilt a very good evening of ours.

McDonald's
17635 64 ave, Surrey, BC V3S1Z2

featured_reviews.review_id:
Only ordered 2 mcflurries and a medium Fry But Had to wait for the food about 35mins. They kept on prioritizing the doordash orders and the people that ordered a lot of food.

Then when the food came out, the Fries came out to be stale and cold. We asked fries and they gave us new fries plus since we waited so long my friend asked for free chicken nuggets. They gave the free chicken nuggets.

Was it really worth sitting and waiting for half an hour for just a simple order? I don't think so. It's not called fast food for no reason.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I would give zero stars if I could.  First off, this location has never been open until midnight.   Doors are locked at 10.  Drive through is not 24 hours either.   I have never been through this Drive through without having to "pull up and park" because the order wasn't ready.   Even for 2 teas!!  They often get orders wrong to the point where it's a running joke between my husband, the neighbors and I.  Customer service is also out of the question.  Very rude staff.  Except for one sweet older lady (not old just older than the other staff I've seen)  Not sure her name but she's absolutely delightful.... so that's a plus.  There's  your one star....
Today I waited in a long lineup in 32deg weather for nothing.  They didn't have earl grey tea apparently (although I was asked to repeat myself so many times I feel they just said that cause he didn't want to ask me to repeat it again.) I got regular tea instead.  Get to the window and I'm told they actually don't have the milkshake I ordered for my husband.  So they would give me a discount on the coffee.   I said I didn't order coffee.  (After all the "to do" about it, how did that get messed up!?)  He tells me they don't have any tea at all.  Seriously!?  I waited half an hour, trapped in the drive through and they have nothing I ordered!?  Waste of time.  I hate this location.

featured_reviews.review_id: These guys advertise as drive thru open 24 hours. But they are not, I went there today at 3:30am after a night out, I can see employees inside but there were cones kept on drive through blocking for cars to go in, so I check it from the other side and asked the gentleman whether they are open he said "Nope we are not" and "you are in the wrong way" what's up with the attitude, your website shows you are open and it allowed me to do mobile order for this location. So I don't understand the attitude.

Went in the drive thru at 11:45 to order. The lady at the front says we are closing at 12 so cannot take your order.
Then the guy says there's a problem in the system and then something wrong with the till.
Bro! It is your job to serve the guest if your service hours are till 12. Ridiculous service, ridiculous people. I would have given 0 stars if there's an option.
